<TEXT>
the alleged mastermind behind the 
hijacking of kuwait airways flight 422 is a longtime fugitive from 
justice linked to two earlier hijacks 
imad mughniyeh 36 is one of four suspects wanted by the us 
justice department in the hijacking of a twa airliner on june 14 
1985 by shiite moslem extremists a us navy diver was killed and 
39 americans were held hostage for 17 days before being freed after 
syrian intervention 
in washington a reagan administration official said another man 
wanted in the united states in the twa hijacking was believed to be 
a hijacker on the kuwaiti plane 
the official speaking on condition of anonymity said the man 
hasan izzaldin was named in a 1987 federal indictment charging 
him and three others with conspiracy to commit air piracy murder 
and assault in the hijacking 
western intelligence agencies also believe mughniyeh was 
involved in the december 1984 hijacking of a kuwaiti airliner to 
tehran that left two americans dead 
iranian security forces stormed the plane after five days the 
hijackers disappeared and tehran has issued no word about them 
western sources speaking on condition of anonymity said 
mughniyeh is the leader of a clan one of several in the bekaa 
valley of eastern lebanon that control the drug trade in there 
he also is chief of security for the proiranian hezbollah or 
party of god in lebanon hezbollah is considered by western and 
lebanese intelligence agencies to be the umbrella organization for 
groups holding foreigners hostages in lebanon 
mughniyehs cousin and brotherinlaw is one of the three 
shiites among the 17 imprisoned in kuwait who have been sentenced 
to death 
western observers have said it is this family connection that 
has fueled mughniyehs mission to free the 17 terrorists 
the kuwaitis have identified the condemned man as elias saab 
but his real name is hussein ali badreddin he entered kuwait on a 
forged iraqi passport western intelligence authorities said 
ever since badreddin was arrested in kuwait mughniyeh has tried 
to free him 
mughniyeh dropped out of sight in beirut several weeks ago 
according to wellinformed sources who asked not to be identified 
one of hezbollahs factions is the islamic jihad or islamic 
holy war the shiite group holding foreigners hostage in lebanon 
it has said it would free the americans they hold if kuwait frees 
the 17 terrorists 
kuwait has refused and the hijacking of the kuwaiti airliner 
which was taken first to iran then to cyprus and finally to 
algeria has not changed that stance 
at one point during talks in cyprus palestinian negotiators 
said the hijackers offered to release half their hostages if kuwait 
freed the three among the 17 who had been sentenced to death 
mughniyehs cousin is among the three 
the cypriots acting on kuwaiti advice rejected the offer but 
it underlined mughniyehs suspected role in the hijacking 
western intelligence sources believe that mughniyeh joined the 
hijacked kuwaiti airliner in mashhad northeastern iran when it 
landed there after it was seized during a flight from bangkok to 
kuwait 
