<TEXT>
airlines are deliberately discriminating against 
blind people by forcing them to switch seats under the guise of 
safety while lacking a uniform seating policy blind activists 
contend 
their complaint follows the second arrest in as many weeks 
involving the seating of blind people on airlines 
in the latst incident james gashel director of governmental 
affairs for the national federation of the blind who is blind was 
taken into custody thursday at ohare international airport after 
he refused to leave his seat in an emergency exit row on a united 
airlines flight bound from chicago to denver 
united attorneys later withdrew the complaint alleging criminal 
trespass pending a review of the case and gashel was released 
said chicago police sgt robert degraff 
gashel 41 who was on his way to a conference in boise idaho 
says united knew he was blind when they assigned him the seat and 
ordered him to move to harass him 
im not a safety hazard to anybody so i dont believe that 
theres a basis for requiring me to move he said in a telephone 
interview from ohare late thursday i didnt like being singled 
out that way 
mr gashel was adamant in his refusal to leave or to change 
seats and united susbequently canceled the flight the sergeant 
said 
the dc8 with 200 passengers was scheduled to leave at 3 pm 
cdt passengers were put on a later flight which left at 426 pm 
said united spokesman joe hopkins 
hopkins said uniteds policy is not to seat blind people in 
emergency exit row seats because theyre normally not manned by 
crew members if there were a fire in the wing area the blind 
person might be unable to assess the situation 
also if we had to evacuate the plane it could slow the 
evacuation hopkins said adding that the federal aviation 
administration says plane evacuations must take no longer than 90 
seconds 
i dont know the mechanics of how he got that seat hopkins 
said once we realized what had happened we attempted to 
relocate him to conform to our policies 
in a similar incident a blind attorney from iowa was arrested 
march 31 on a midway airlines flight at the washingtonnational 
airport after she refused to move from a smoking section seat into 
an exit area seat said mary ellen reihing a spokeswoman for the 
baltimorebased federation 
it is becoming clear to us that the pattern is deliberate our 
leaders some who move with canes are being assigned those 
seats and being forced to move from them it is a clear attempt to 
be be harassed she said 
some airlines say we cant sit in exit rows some say we have 
to sit in exit rows said steven benson president of the 
federations illinois chapter we regard it as blatantly 
discriminatory 
hopkins denied the allegation saying theyre after the 
publicity 
gashel meantime planned to fly to denver today on another 
airline 
i dont believe in going along with violating a law he 
said i wasnt causing a delay i feel sad that united airlines 
caused a delay for other passengers and me i feel about as sad 
about that as other passengers 
how do i get justice 
