<TEXT>
the first returnfiling season under the 
broadest us income tax overhaul in history closes out at 
midnight but the average american will have to work 20 more days 
to keep federal state and local tax collectors at bay for another 
year 
tax freedom day will come may 5 the latest date since the 
tax foundation began counting a halfcentury ago if the government 
took every penny you earned until your share of the total tax 
burden were paid the foundation reckons you would have to work 
the first 126 days of 1988 just to meet those obligations 
thirty years ago tax freedom day fell on april 10 
several million americans didnt have time to fret about such 
fanciful calculations they were working up to the eleventh hour on 
their 1987 returns and many were sure to be standing in line in 
front of mail drops as the midnight filing deadline approached 
any return not postmarked by midnight and carrying the correct 
postage could be subject to a late filing penalty 
the internal revenue service cautioned taxpayers not to ignore 
the deadline even if they cant afford to pay all the taxes they 
owe although failure to pay on time can result in one penalty 
failure to file can bring an additional one 
the irs estimated that about 62 million couples and individuals 
would apply for an automatic fourmonth extension of the filing 
deadline by mailing form 4868 with a check for their estimated 
taxes that is up about 20 percent from last year due in large 
part to all the taxlaw changes that must be reflected on returns 
being filed this year 
congress 1986 overhaul of the tax law changed more than 2700 
provisions and led the irs to create 48 new forms but the typical 
individual was unaffected by the great majority of those changes 
and has to use few if any of the new forms 
nevertheless taxpayers have been sufficiently confused about 
the new law to telephone more than 17 million questions to the irs 
and to order record numbers of explanatory publications from the 
agency 
the new law reduced tax rates significantly and nearly doubled 
the personal exemption to 1900 but it reduced or eliminated a 
number of deductions and exemptions including those for sales 
taxes medical expenses moving consumer interest and individual 
retirement accounts 
one of the biggest sources of confusion was the requirement that 
every employee file a revised w4 form so that the amount of tax 
withheld could be adjusted to mirror the new law many workers 
found the new form so complex that the irs had to revise it again 
eventually the irs announced it would not penalize any worker 
for failing to pay enough tax in advance on 1987 wages 
the irs itself is having trouble keeping up with the new law as 
recently as thursday it was issuing advice to taxpayers on how 
they might avoid penalties that were caused by getting the wrong 
answer to a tax question from an irs telephone assistor about 
28 of every 100 callers are getting wrong answers the irs concedes 
economists for the tax foundation say benefits of the 
acrosstheboard tax cut enacted in 1981 have been wiped out by tax 
increases voted in 1982 1983 1984 and 1987 
like the cheshire cat in alice in wonderland nothing 
remains but the smile the foundation said 
tax freedom day calculations by the tax foundation a washington 
research organization assume that individuals pay all taxes 
including those collected from corporations the economists simply 
divide all federal state and local tax collections among taxpayers 
and assume that every penny earned each year goes to government 
until tax obligations are satisfied 
last year tax freedom day was may 4 this years may 5 date is 
two days later because 1988 is a leap year 
if taxes were viewed on the basis of an eighthour work day the 
foundation said the average taxpayer would have to work 1 hour and 
50 minutes a day to pay federal taxes and another 55 minutes for 
state and local taxes thats two minutes longer for federal taxes 
than in 1987 but the same as last year for state and local taxes 
</TEXT>
