the graham family is seeking a corporate 
charter change to tighten its control of the washington post 
company a move aimed at preventing any outside takeover 
the proposal to be voted on by stockholders may 12 is a 
reaction to efforts to take control of media general inc based in 
richmond va by hollywood producer burt sugarman post officials 
said today 
the post has two classes of stock one controlled by the graham 
family and the other traded publicly 
the system was designed so that no takeover could occur without 
agreement of the family however the number of publicly traded 
shares is larger than the total owned by the family so if the two 
types of stock were voted together the graham family shares would 
be a minority 
no attempt to acquire the post has been made company officials 
said 
however sugarman is challenging a similar twoclass stock 
system in the media general case 
so post officials say they are proposing a charter amendment 
that will clearly state that any attempt to take over their company 
would have to have separate approval of a majority of each class of 
stock 
