cracks are appearing in the underground 
palestinian leadership over how to wage a campaign of resistance 
against israels occupation of the west bank and gaza strip 
the divisions are emerging at a time when the frequency and size 
of street clashes is diminishing and the nature of the 
confrontation is changing into more of an economic test of wills 
there are two basic splits in palestinian ranks 
the islamic resistance movement is at odds with the mainstream 
palestine liberation organization factions on the issue of 
convening an international conference to negotiate peace 
the communists in a dispute over tactics have pulled out of 
the ploaffiliated underground command the united national 
leadership of the uprising 
the underground has announced weekly action programs in a series 
of leaflets but starting in early march there have been multiple 
versions some making conflicting demands on the 15 million 
residents of the occupied west bank and gaza strip 
in the latest handbill no 13 one version calls for three days 
of general strikes to mark prisoners day while another 
