lebanons economy once the most flourishing in the middle east 
has been hit hard by 13 years of violence 
the pound which rated 25 to the dollar before the outbreak of 
the civil war in 1975 has declined sharply against foreign 
currencies pushing prices sky high in a nation that imports more 
than 85 percent of its needs 
