convention because of offices they hold or held in all 644 of 
these delegates who are free to make or dissolve their commitments 
to presidential candidates as they see fit are to attend the 
convention 
dukakis gore and simon are super delegates as is missouri rep 
richard gephardt who dropped out of the presidental race last 
month 
the remaining 85 percent of the delegates to the convention 
3518 are getting there through the primaries or caucuses in 
which they are required to pledge themselves to support a 
presidential candidate or declare that they are uncommitted 
although dukakis delegate lead is becoming formidable his 
total represents just 40 percent of the 2082 delegates needed to 
win the partys presidential nomination 
jackson whose landslide victory in michigan on march 26 
momentarily pushed him into the lead in delegates now has 7301 
delegates in the ap count that includes 45 super delegates 
gore has 41155 delegates including 41 super delegates and 
simon has 1835 delegates overall including 285 super delegates 
more than 600 delegates are uncommitted including about 400 
from the ranks of the partys political professionals 
