<TEXT>
america on friday vetoed a security 
council resolution that urged israel to stop deporting palestinians 
from the occupied territories saying the measure lacked balance 
arab diplomats denounced the action and said it hurt the latest 
us initiative to promote middle east peace talks 
fourteen of the councils 15 members voted for the resolution 
and britain made an unusually harsh speech against israels policy 
of deporting palestinians allegedly linked to disturbances in the 
occupied west bank of the jordan river and gaza strip 
british ambassador john birch called the deportations brutal 
and often indiscriminate actions and said they are immoral 
illegal and politically selfdefeating 
world opinion has been shocked and disgusted rightly so by 
the widespread suffering of the civilian population of all ages and 
both sexes in the territories he said 
arab league spokesman clovis maksoud said the veto mortally 
wounded the us peace initiative and would encourage israel to 
mistreat the 15 million palestinians living under israeli 
occupation 
