under un auspices that would include the plo and the five 
permanent members of the security council the united states 
soviet union china britain and france permanent members have 
veto power 
other members of the council are algeria argentina brazil 
italy japan nepal senegal west germany yugoslavia and zambia 
israel refuses to talk with the plo which it considers a 
terrorist organization and prime minister yitzhak shamir has 
opposed an international peace conference saying it might try to 
force concessions that would jeopardize israels security 
despite its veto the united states has been critical of 
israels handling of violence in the occupied territories 
on jan 5 it cast a rare vote against israeli joining the rest 
of the security council in approving a resolution urging the jewish 
state to refrain from an earlier round of deportations 
israel defied the resolution and deported four palestinian 
activists to lebanon 
the united states on jan 14 declined to use its veto to protect 
israel and abstained as the council passed a resolution urging 
israel to let the deportees return 
okun said friday the latest resolution was redundant 
