<TEXT>
wholesale prices jumped 06 percent in march 
the biggest increase in 11 months the government said today in a 
report that added to jitters on financial markets about inflation 
and the health of the economy 
the march increase more than erased a 02 percent drop in 
feburaryif the march rate held for 12 months the fullyear 
wholesale inflation rate would be 7 percent compared with 22 
percent for all of 1987 
the dow jones industrial average of 30 bluechip industrial 
stocks which staged its fifth biggest loss and dropped more than 
101 points thursday in reaction to disappointing trade figures 
fell 22 points to 198375 in the first 90 minutes of trading today 
