activity that energy prices which had been falling at an annual 
rate of 17 percent rose 09 percent last month their first 
increase since august 
food prices after dropping 11 percent in february advanced by 
07 percent last month for the first three months of the year 
beef and veal prices climbed 436 percent 
overall wholesale prices rose at an annual rate of 31 percent 
from january through march 
the widespread nature of these price changes suggests that 
inflation pressures may be intensifying said donald ratajczak a 
