a federal judge friday blocked investors led 
by britains brian c beazer from proceeding with a 17 billion 
hostile takeover of koppers co but the judge left the door open 
for beazer to salvage the proposed deal 
us district judge maurice b cohill jr said that the novel 
role played by shearson lehman hutton inc in the takeover 
apparently requires the investment banking firm to file financial 
disclosure statements just like any other bidder shearson did not 
make the filings 
