general motors corp chairman roger smith 
received at least 22 million for 1987 in salary exercised stock 
options and stock grants the nations largest automaker reported 
friday in its proxy statement 
smith received 867000 in salary earned 513121 exercising 
stock options and was awarded a stock bonus worth 800000 when it 
was granted on dec 7 the stock issued in blocks over a 
threeyear period that began in january is worth considerably more 
now 
gm president robert stempel received at least 12 million for 
1987 517000 in salary 73523 on exercised stock options and 
600000 in the stock bonus stempel became president in august 
when he replaced the retired f james mcdonald 
in all gm paid 136 million in 1987 salaries to its top 58 
executives and gave stock awards worth 162 million on dec 7 and 
211 million on friday to 4961 executives 
ford motor co the no 2 automaker paid 2479 million in 
bonuses for 1987 to 5166 executives it reported in a proxy 
statement mailed tuesday 
ford vice chairman harold poling earned nearly 11 million in 
1987 808697 in salary 2 million in cash bonuses and nearly 
81 million on exercised stock options 
ford chairman donald petersen who exercised no stock options 
received 28 million in cash bonuses and 929934 in salary 
gms profit rose to 36 billion in 1987 from 295 billion in 
1986 but for the second year in a row it earned too little on its 
us automaking business to pay profitsharing to its 350000 
hourly us workers 
the outcry over the millions of dollars executives received in 
bonuses for 1986 prompted gms board of directors in 1987 to switch 
to an allstock bonus and spread each stock grant over several 
years 
united auto workers union president owen bieber and vice 
president donald ephlin said the 1987 compensation received by top 
gm executives still cant be justified rationally and constitutes 
an insult to common sense and fairness 
during a time when gms automaking business is earning so 
little they said in a statement we will leave the executives to 
forego all increases and supplementary awards in the spirit of 
shared sacrifice 
ford distributed a record 636 million in profitsharing checks 
in march to more than 156000 hourly and salaried employees an 
average of more than 4000 each 
